Program: Outlook
Title: 17/03/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p006lyly
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 18 Mar 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. Refugees United part two; waterhole wildlife photographs; unrequited love blog Refugees United Hundreds of thousand of refugees around the world become separated from family and friends after fleeing their countries. A new project, Refugees United, uses the internet to bring families together. For Outlook, Helen Clegg hears one of their success stories - that of Yonas, a Zimbabwean refugee in Rio de Janeiro. Wildlife photographs at a price South African photographer Greg du Toit tells us how he sat in a muddy African water hole for hours on end hoping for a close-up of lions. Eventually he was rewarded with a stunning set of pictures, but he picked up some unpleasant diseases on the way. Love Blog Giuseppe Carlo fell in love with an Italian woman he met via a social networking site. When his feelings weren't returned, he decided to start a love blog about the woman who stole his heart. Outlook reporter Dany Mitzman meets Giuseppe to find out more. Show less